messages.content: What is the purpose of efficiency-nodes-comfyui?
efficiency-nodes-comfyui is a set of custom nodes or plugins that extend the functionality of ComfyUI, a GUI that uses stable diffusion models to generate images and videos.
How many image examples are provided in the documentation for efficiency-nodes-comfyui?
The documentation provides 11 image examples demonstrating the capabilities of efficiency-nodes-comfyui.
What is the arrangement of the image examples in the documentation?
The image examples are arranged in a table with 3 rows and 4 columns, with one empty cell in the last row.
What is the size of each image example in the documentation?
Each image example has a width of 200 pixels.
Are the image examples in the documentation hosted on GitHub?
Yes, the image examples are hosted on GitHub, specifically in the repository of jags111/efficiency-nodes-comfyui.
Do the image examples have timestamps in their file names?
Yes, each image example file name includes a timestamp indicating when it was created or saved.
What is the file format of the image examples in the documentation?
The image examples are in PNG format, as indicated by the .png extension in their file names.
